flowchart LR
  %% Core user interaction and pipeline
  U[User (Browser)] --> UI[Index.razor UI<br/>(Enter repo URL, optional PAT)]
  UI -->|Repo URL / PAT| AgentService[AgentService<br/>(orchestrator)]

  subgraph FetchAndPrep ["Data Preparation"]
    RepoSvc[RepoService<br/>(GitHub Contents API)] --> Files[Fetched files<br/>(README + code/text)]
    Files --> Chunker[TextChunker<br/>(sentence-based chunks, overlap)]
    Chunker --> Chunks[Chunks (~300–500 words)]
  end

  subgraph EmbeddingAndStore ["Vectorization & Store"]
    Chunks --> EmbeddingSvc[EmbeddingService<br/>(Azure OpenAI embeddings — batched)]
    EmbeddingSvc --> VectorStore[VectorStore<br/>(in-memory, cosine similarity)]
  end

  subgraph ReasoningLoop ["RAG → LLM → Reflection Loop"]
    AgentService -->|retrieve| VectorStore
    VectorStore --> Rag[RagService<br/>(top-K retrieval + prompt)]
    Rag --> Chat[Azure OpenAI Chat<br/>(analysis model)]
    Chat --> Answer[Initial Answer (Markdown)]

    Answer --> Reflection[ReflectionService<br/>(LLM self-review & rewrite)]
    Reflection --> Evaluation[EvaluationService<br/>(LLM scores 1–10)]
    Evaluation -- score < 8 --> Reflection
    Evaluation -- score ≥ 8 --> Final[Final Answer (Markdown)]
  end

  Final --> UI

  %% Side panels: technologies and run instructions
  Tech[Technologies / Libraries:
  • .NET 8 (Blazor Server)
  • Azure.AI.OpenAI (chat + embeddings)
  • Microsoft.SemanticKernel (conceptual usage)
  • Markdig (Markdown → HTML)
  • HttpClient (GitHub API)
  • In-memory vector store (custom)
  ]

  Run[How to run (quick):
  1) Set Azure OpenAI values in __appsettings.json__:
     - AzureOpenAI:Endpoint, ApiKey, ChatDeployment, EmbeddingDeployment
  2) (Optional) Use GitHub PAT for private repos (enter in UI)
  3) Build & run:
     dotnet restore
     dotnet build
     dotnet run --project Analyst.Agent.Host
  4) Open browser → https://localhost:5001, enter repo URL, click Analyze
  ]

  UI -.-> Tech
  UI -.-> Run

